17/01/2005
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Romanian Prime Minister Calin Tariceanu traveled to Budapest on Monday (17 January), his first visit abroad since assuming office last month.
Tariceanu is holding talks with Hungarian counterpart Ferenc Gyurcsany, President Ferenc Madl and parliamentary officials.
In other news, Romanian Defence Minister Theodor Atanasiu said on Saturday that Bucharest would decide after the 30 January elections in Iraq whether to retain a military presence there.
Atanasiu told reporters he plans to visit the Romanian troops in March.
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 17/01/05;
Rompres, Mediafax - 15/01/05;
Nine o'clock - 14/01/05)
